tip.text: The shabu shabu is good here with a robust tonkotsu soup. I like the minced chicken with the addition of soft cartilage giving it a crunchy texture. Sauces come at $2 a person (refillable though).
You can never go wrong with beef cheek stew.
Lamb chops done just right with just enough gaminess so that you know that you are eating lamb. Really tender and not fatty at all.

tip.text: Dinner last night. Lively and crowded with families. The mapo doufu was not bad, quite tasty but nowhere near the real szechuan ma (not enough szechuan pepper). They have dim sum at night too.
Super comfortable hospital/hotel with very attentive nurses. Extensive menu of food to chose from. Even the toiletries are hotel quality.
They differentiate themselves from other mookata places, serving premium meats such as kurobuta pork and wagyu beef. Good quality meat was tasty and the soup was flavoursome with meat drippings.
Lobster sashimi was so yummy and fresh. The head was used to make lobster porridge (which was very flavoursome by the way) after we were done with the sashimi.

tip.text: Lamb rack is done just right. Steak is juicy and delish.
We had smoked salmon with poached eggs (smooth runny yolks) and mushroom fritata. Both went very well with the aromatic latte.
Can't go wrong with the sashimi here - always fresh and sweet.
Delicious wagyu beef and kurobuta pork here. You'll have to GIY (grill it yourself) though. The soup that comes with set tastes like it's MSG laden though.
Tried the siew mai, har gao, and fried carrot cake. Average quality but not too bad for food that you can find at a hospital. Would come back here again if I'm at Mt E Novena
